# Repository Structure

**Project**: WebRTC Engineering — demo applications repository

> **Single Source of Truth**: For the complete and detailed repository structure, naming conventions, and workflow standards, refer to [docs/01-repository-structure.md](../../docs/01-repository-structure.md).

## Quick Summary

- **`src/NN-category/demo-name/`**: Self-contained WebRTC demo apps grouped by area (fundamentals, signaling, small projects, etc.).
- **`docs/`**: Architecture notes, RFC summaries, diagrams, and reviews.
- **`experiments/`**: Bandwidth, codec, and load-testing experiments.
- **`assets/`**: Images, diagrams, and media assets.
- **`tools/`**: PowerShell maintenance scripts (`psscripts/`).

When writing or updating public-facing structure (for example `README.md` or `docs/01-repository-structure.md`), do not list or mention any internal-only paths.

## Preserved archives

- `.archive/` contains legacy tooling and old content. Leave it as-is unless Swamy explicitly asks to migrate or clean it.
- Routine parity, docs, and CI reviews should focus on active `src/` demos and governance/tooling consistency.
